claim.claim-text:
1. A method for securely completing a service transaction, comprising:
receiving a request for a reservation for a reserved service to be provided by a specific service provider, the request received at a device associated with a customer;
receiving, at a preauthorization system, a request for preauthorizing payment of the reserved service to be provided by the specific service provider at the reservation using a credit account of the customer;
generating preauthorization information including a total maximum amount of preauthorized credit for the transaction with the specific service provider and unique transaction identification information, wherein the total maximum amount is dynamically detennined at least based on one metric by the preauthorization system;
generating reservation information including a date and time the reserved service is to be provided by the specific service provider to the customer at a specific service provider location to satisfy the reservation;
storing the reservation information and the preauthorization information on a database remote from the specific service provider;
transmitting the reservation and preauthorization information to the specific service provider;
using at least some of the preauthorization information at the specific service provider, after the reserved service is provided to the customer by the specific service provider, to generate payment information, which information includes at least the unique transaction identification information; and
transmitting the payment information to the database, the database completing payment to the specific service provider for provided services up to the total maximum amount without the service provider being provided access to the customer's credit account information.

11. A reservation and secure payment method, the steps comprising:
receiving a request for provision of a service from a customer;
verifying availability of a requested reservation for the service to be provided by a specific service provider at a service provider location, reserving the service with the specific service provider and generating reservation information, the information including a date and time the reserved service is to be provided by the specific service provider to the customer;
generating, by a preauthorization system, preauthorization information, the information including a total amount of preauthorized credit to be charged on a credit account of the customer and available to pay for the reserved service with the specific service provider to satisfy the reservation and unique transaction identification information, wherein the total amount is dynamically determined at least based on one metric by the preauthorization system;
storing the reservation information and the preauthorization information on a database remote from the specific service provider;
transmitting at least some of the reservation and the preauthorization information to the specific service provider through use of a network;
using at least some of the preauthorization information at the specific service provider, after the service is provided to the customer by the specific service provider to satisfy the reservation, to generate at least some payment information, which information includes at least the unique transaction identification information; and
transmitting the payment information to the database to complete payment of charges associated with service provided at the reservation by the specific service provider up to the total amount and without the service provider being provided with access to the customer's credit account information.

23. A device for receiving reservation and preauthorization information and securely transmitting payment information to a service provider, comprising:
a memory;
a display;
a mechanism to receive a previously generated reservation with a specific service provider and preauthorization information from a remote database, the reservation information including a date and time the reserved service is to be provided by the specific service provider and the preauthorization information including a total amount of preauthorized credit available to pay for reserved services provided by the specific service provider to satisfy the reservation from a customer's credit account and unique transaction identification information, wherein the total amount is dynamically determined at least based on one metric by the mechanism;
a mechanism to generate at least some payment information after the reserved services are provided by the specific service provider at a specific service provider location to the customer pursuant to the reservation using received preauthorization information, the payment information including at least the unique transaction identification information and the cost of services rendered up to the total amount;
a mechanism to transmit the payment information to a remote device; and
wherein the service provider is not provided access to the customer's credit account information.

32. A system for generating and securely storing certain reservation and preauthorization information, comprising:
receiving a request for a reservation for a service with a specific service provider from a customer;
receiving, at a preauthorization system, a request to preauthorize up to a predetermined amount for the service to be provided by the specific service provider at the reservation using credit account information of the customer;
storing at least some generated reservation and preauthorization information on a database remote from the service provider, wherein the preauthorization information includes the total amount of preauthorization credit available to pay for reserved services to be provided by the specific service provider and unique transaction identification information, wherein the total amount is dynamically determined at least based on one metric by the preauthorization system;
transmitting at least some reservation information and preauthorization information stored on the remote database to the service provider;
using the received preauthorization information after the service is provided by the specific service provider at a service provider location to generate at least some payment information, which information includes the unique transaction identification information; and
transmitting the payment information up to the total amount to the database to complete payment of charges associated with service provided at the reservation and without the service provider being provided with access to the customer's credit account information.

42. A network for completing secure service transactions, comprising:
receiving a request for a reservation for a service to be provided by a specific service provider at a device from a customer and granting a reservation;
receiving information concerning future payment for the service to be provided by the specific service provider at the reservation using account information of the customer;
storing at least some reservation and payment information on a database and associated server remote from a service provider, wherein the stored payment information includes a total amount of preauthorized credit available to satisfy payment of the reserved service provided by the specific service provider and unique transaction identification information, wherein the total maximum amount is dynamically determined at least based on one metric by the server;
transmitting at least some reservation information to the specific service provider;
retrieving from the database at least some payment information after the service is provided by the specific service provider at a service provider location to satisfy the reservation;
generating service payment information, which information includes unique transaction identification information, at the service provider; and
transmitting the payment information to the database to complete payment up to the total amount of charges associated with service provided at the reservation and without the service provider being provided with access to the customer's credit account information.
